            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "No. You're misunderstanding how it works.\r\n\r\n```\r\ncdef int test(self) nogil except -1:\r\n    return -1   # should raise\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhat this says is: if Cython raises an error, then it'll use a value of -1 to indicate it to the caller.\r\nIt does not say that a value of -1 is converted into an exception. All `return -1` will do is confuse the caller (because it expects an exception to be set).\r\n\r\nWhat you want is something like:\r\n```\r\ncdef int test(self) nogil except -1:\r\n    raise ValueError\r\n```",
