            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> So except -1 is just a way for caller to realize that it needs to propagate the exception raised inside the cdef function.\r\n\r\nYes.\r\n\r\n> If there's no exception detected, it behaves like a normal cdef function (i.e. just returns -1 and that's it)?\r\n\r\nThis really isn't well-defined. It expects there to be an exception if you return -1. It may or may not check. You shouldn't rely on it.\r\n\r\nIf `-1` is a legitimate value to return then you should use `except ?-1` instead (which says \"a value of -1 might be an exception\")",
